---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About HtownGuide — An independent guide to Houston"
  description="HtownGuide is an independent, locally-edited guide to Houston, Texas. Made for visitors, World Cup fans, and Houstonians who keep finding new corners of the city."
>
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 pt-20 pb-24">
    <span class="block text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-[color:var(--color-clay)] mb-4">About</span>
    <h1 class="font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] text-5xl sm:text-6xl tracking-tight leading-[0.95] mb-10 text-balance">
      An independent guide to <em class="italic font-normal text-[color:var(--color-clay)]">a sprawling, underrated city</em>.
    </h1>

    <div class="space-y-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-ink-soft)] text-pretty">
      <p>
        Houston has more good food per capita than almost any city in America. It hosts NASA, a Texas Medical Center the size of downtown Dallas, the largest livestock show in the world, and three major-league franchises. It's the fourth-largest U.S. city by population. And it consistently shows up nowhere on travel-guide lists.
      </p>
      <p>
        HtownGuide exists to fix that — or at least make a small dent. We're a locally-built, independently-edited guide written for visitors and locals alike. No corporate sponsorship. No tourism-board talking points. Just the recommendations we'd give a friend.
      </p>
      <p>
        We earn small commissions when readers book hotels or tours through our links — it keeps the site running and the recommendations honest. We only ever recommend places we'd actually go to ourselves.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you have a place we should know about, or you spot something wrong, <a href="/contact" class="text-[color:var(--color-clay)] underline decoration-1 underline-offset-4">get in touch</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
